Police in Limpopo are searching for the mother of a toddler who was found abandoned in one of the food outlets in the city of Polokwane on Saturday. The baby, who is alleged to be a few days old, was taken to hospital for medical assistance. Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe is appealing to anyone with information to contact the police. “It is alleged that at about 13:00 one of the customers at the outlet went to the toilet and on arrival she was shocked to find a toddler placed on the floor wearing a jersey and wrapped with a blanket. She then alerted employees who immediately informed the police,” says Ngoepe.